Interface JkArtifactLocator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    JkArtifactProducer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JkStandardFileArtifactProducer, JkSuppliedFileArtifactProducer

    public interface JkArtifactLocator
    Defines methods for enumerating artifacts files likely to be produced.

    • Method Detail

      • getArtifactPath

        java.nio.file.Path getArtifactPath(JkArtifactId artifactId)
        Returns file ofSystem path where is supposed to be produced the specified artifact file id. This method is supposed to only returns the file reference and not generate it.

      • getMainArtifactId

        default JkArtifactId getMainArtifactId()
        Returns the main artifact file id for this producer. By default it returns a artifact file id with no classifier and 'jar" getExtension.

      • getMainArtifactExt

        default java.lang.String getMainArtifactExt()
        Returns the extension used by the main artifact.

      • getArtifactIds

        default java.util.List<JkArtifactId> getArtifactIds()
        Returns all the artifact ids likely to be produced by this artifact producer. By default it returns a single element list containing the main artifact file id

      • getMainArtifactPath

        default java.nio.file.Path getMainArtifactPath()
        Returns the main artifact path.

      • getMissingFiles

        default java.util.List<java.nio.file.Path> getMissingFiles()
        Returns non existing files matching for artifacts.
